title: What's to blame for Australia's obesity rate?
text:
What's to blame for Australia's obesity rate? Share 
Australia's medical colleges are demanding the Federal Government take action to prevent obesity. 
The Government has been criticised for an unacceptable lack of national policy on obesity. 
However Australia has had 40 years of health food programs, messages and campaigns. 
Why haven't they worked? Broadcast: Mon 13 Feb 2017, 9:30am Published: Mon 13 Feb 2017, 2:03pm
